Introduction

This is an automatically generated report based around Mapping the SARS-CoV-2 spike glycoprotein-derived peptidome presented by HLA class II on dendritic cells. The raw data is accessed from PRIDE and the supplemental file mmc2.csv.

It simply takes each of the peptides listed in the file. Looks at the Scan it came from and then tries to access an do some analysis plots. This tests that the raw data can be loaded and accessed. A plot of the predicted fragmantation ions for the peptide is also shown. The plots are either standard from base R functions or come from protviz.

The analysis is set up to use an RServer in a docker container and uses RMarkdown to generate the reports.
